880. em tibi hommem, ‘there's your man.‘ For em see v. 431, and Sonnenschein's Rudens p. 189. The Parasite pushes the door farther open, or draws back a curtain and shews the triclinium to Artemona. They remain unseen to the banqueters up to ν. 909.

The conversation between the three characters at table is now resumed. Artemona listens to what they say, and unheard by them makes her own comments on their remarks.
